article.description: Haws leads BYU over Eastern Kentucky 90-76
article.headline: Haws leads BYU over Eastern Kentucky 90-76
article.linkText: Haws leads BYU over Eastern Kentucky 90-76
article.story: PROVO, Utah -- Tyler Haws scored 26 points and three other players reached double figures to lead BYU to a 90-76 victory over Eastern Kentucky on Saturday night. BYU led 32-30 at the break and they opened the second half with a 17-4 run, capped by Haws' 3-pointer, to take a 49-36 lead with 14:51 to play. Haws' fourth trey made it 64-41 with 11:15 left. Chase Fischer scored 20 points, Anson Winder had 19 and Kyle Collinsworth chipped in 11 for BYU (5-2). Haws and Fischer were each 4 of 8 from beyond the arc. Eric Stutz made a pair of free throws to give Eastern Kentucky its only lead, 12-10. Ja'Mill Powell drained a 3-pointer to tie it at 30 with 48 seconds left in the first half. Frank Bartley IV answered for BYU, and they led the rest of the way. Powell scored 26 points to lead Eastern Kentucky (4-1).
